* [X] Mouth also function as food processing facility, taking over this function from Torso
* [X] FatCells have an energy buffer proportional to their size, apart from the fat mass
	- [X] when energy is used in the body, it is subtracted from this buffer
	- [X] when food is processed by mouth, first thing to fill up is the energy buffer, then the excess goes into fat mass
	- [X] if the energy buffer is depleted, fat mass will be used to fill it up
* [X] when energy is required, it will be subtracted uniformly from all existing fat cells, as much as possible, to keep them balanced.

